Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.82,0:00:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Young ones, it’s true \Nthat the more you understand Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.72,0:00:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the more you love him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.86,0:00:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And what a blessing you have \Nif your family worships Jehovah with you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.73,0:00:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and teaches you how to draw close to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.90,0:00:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But some young ones \Nhave had to build their faith
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.63,0:00:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,without their family’s support.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.50,0:00:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to the experience of Ersi Royer \Nfrom the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.57,0:00:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What spiritual decision did she face \Nat just 14 years old?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.08,0:00:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And what did she do \Nthat illustrates the value
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.01,0:00:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of deep personal study?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.92,0:00:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Growing up,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.55,0:00:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it wasn’t the typical,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.56,0:00:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“My mom is a pioneer, my dad is an elder,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.16,0:00:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re doing great in the congregation.”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.49,0:00:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,My family life wasn’t the best,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.33,0:00:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so why would I want to do this religion \Nthat nobody is happy
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.40,0:00:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in our family with?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.00,0:00:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think that can make you feel
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.50,0:00:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,very alone or odd
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.34,0:00:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,or awkward or secluded.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.21,0:01:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that time, \NI was graduating eighth grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.31,0:01:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There were dances;
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.88,0:01:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,friends were hanging out, going to parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.85,0:01:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember thinking: \N‘Wow, these look like really nice kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.52,0:01:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why aren’t I doing that?’
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.36,0:01:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I hadn’t really delved into the Bible enough \Nto answer questions
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.36,0:01:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that I really needed to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.60,0:01:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I went in prayer to Jehovah and said: \N“I’m so sorry, but today I’m not a Witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.40,0:01:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to try to prove \Neverything that I’ve been taught is wrong.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.07,0:01:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked him that if he’s real,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.81,0:01:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to help me understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.41,0:01:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went in my room
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.28,0:01:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and shut the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.88,0:01:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I got every book off the shelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.98,0:01:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I started off organized,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.12,0:01:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but by the end of the evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.45,0:01:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I had books \Nall over the place with pages open.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.22,0:01:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The more I kept reading about Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.66,0:01:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the more the next topic would take me \Nto then connect the scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.50,0:01:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus is linked to Jehovah;
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.43,0:01:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the angels are linked to Jehovah; \Nthe resurrection is linked to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.50,0:02:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can’t believe in one thing \Nand not everything else
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.47,0:02:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,if you really want to know the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.68,0:02:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that’s what did it for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.01,0:02:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,especially the scripture in Psalms
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.28,0:02:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,when it said \Nthat ‘you saw even the embryo of me.’
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.92,0:02:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was an emotional scripture for me
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.92,0:02:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,because I thought: \N‘Wow,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.62,0:02:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,‘my parents aren’t doing great \Nin the truth right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.69,0:02:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,‘But Jehovah found a way to find me,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.10,0:02:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and he knew what I could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.93,0:02:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Now I have my answer. \NI don’t have an excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.87,0:02:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Jehovah gave me enough knowledge \Nthat now I’m responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.70,0:02:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I now need to act on that \Nand show my love in return for him.’
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.81,0:02:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Within a week, I found another sister
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.35,0:02:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in the hall that was really helpful \Nin me getting out
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.85,0:02:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in service quite often.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.02,0:02:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t think to this day she ever knew \Nhow much I appreciated that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.39,0:02:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Although things were declining \Nin our family spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.59,0:02:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I was able to get baptized.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.83,0:02:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,As I progressed spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.83,0:03:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I could see that I did not have
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.83,0:03:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the support of my family,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.00,0:03:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but I had to trust that Jehovah \Nwould help me through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.57,0:03:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And at least by the time I got home, \Nif there was an issue,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.34,0:03:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the strength of the meeting \Nand the brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.34,0:03:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and joy that they \Ncouldn’t take away from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.38,0:03:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember I came home one day \Nwith some friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.75,0:03:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a nice day
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.48,0:03:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,—encouraging, upbuilding.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.35,0:03:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We pulled into our driveway; \Nthey dropped me off
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.66,0:03:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and said good-bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.26,0:03:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents were really upset
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.09,0:03:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when they came and met me at the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.46,0:03:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They couldn’t fully understand
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.16,0:03:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,why I was making my decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.87,0:03:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the way I was \Nto serve Jehovah more fully.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.14,0:03:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We just could not agree
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.14,0:03:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,on where my relationship \Nwith Jehovah was going.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.85,0:03:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that point, \NI left with the clothes on my back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.65,0:03:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In a matter of a few minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.32,0:03:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,my life forever changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.76,0:04:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a spiritual aunt that took me in,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.13,0:04:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,helped me gather myself together,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.87,0:04:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and literally fed me, clothed me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.64,0:04:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,helped me spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.04,0:04:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And so then, my support became Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.28,0:04:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.15,0:04:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember that a sister told me years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.08,0:04:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be who you needed when you were young.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.79,0:04:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And so when I look at those little ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.29,0:04:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I look at myself and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.06,0:04:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How could I have benefited
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.49,0:04:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,from someone taking the time for me \Nwhen I was that age?’
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.17,0:04:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve always tried remembering the young ones
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.17,0:04:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,—because that’s just part of who I am—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.07,0:04:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and making sure that they know \Nthat they’re not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.97,0:04:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If there is a young one out there \Nwho isn’t sure
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.44,0:04:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,if this is the truth or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.85,0:04:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like them to know \Nthat Jehovah knows
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.75,0:05:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,who they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.58,0:05:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s finding a way \Nfor them to know him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.45,0:05:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is real, \Nhe knows them by name,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.46,0:05:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,he wants them to live, \Nand he’s fighting for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.63,0:05:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How amazing that young Ersi chose \Nto spend an entire day studying
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.63,0:05:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,—proving to herself \Nthat Jehovah knew her and loved her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.14,0:05:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But this was no onetime study marathon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.11,0:05:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,From there, she worked to develop \Nthe study habits she needed
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.88,0:05:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to endure, grow, \Nand become a spiritual person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.65,0:05:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,She pioneered for several years,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.95,0:05:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and now serves at Bethel \Nwith her husband, Jeff.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.95,0:05:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In my conversation with Ersi, \Nshe expressed her love for her family
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.66,0:05:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and the hope that someday in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.23,0:05:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,she’ll be reunited with them spiritually.
